name: FsF-F1-01D
principle: Data is assigned a globally unique identifier.

name: FsF-F1-02D
principle: Data is assigned a persistent identifier.

name: FsF-F2-01M
column7: summary and keywords) to support data findability.

name: FsF-F3-01M
principle: Metadata includes the identifier of the data it describes.

name: FsF-F4-01M
principle: Metadata is offered in such a way that it can be retrieved programmatically.

name: FsF-A1-01M
principle: Metadata contains access level and access conditions of the data.

name: FsF-A1-02M
principle: Metadata is accessible through a standardized communication protocol.

name: FsF-A1-03D
principle: Data is accessible through a standardized communication protocol.

name: FsF-I1-01M
principle: Metadata is represented using a formal knowledge representation language.

name: FsF-I3-01M
principle: Metadata includes links between the data and its related entities.

name: FsF-R1-01MD
principle: Metadata specifies the content of the data.

name: FsF-R1.1-01M
principle: Metadata includes license information under which data can be reused.

name: FsF-R1.2-01M
principle: Metadata includes provenance information about data creation or generation.

name: FsF-R1.3-01M
principle: Metadata follows a standard recommended by the target research community of the data.

name: FsF-R1.3-02D
principle: Data is available in a file format recommended by the target research community.
